Um... I'm okay with that kind of thing...
\n<Minato Neon>Well, in that case...
...Saying that, she quickly left.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」
\n<Minato Neon>「！？」
I overtook her and confronted her again.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>I'm definitely not a suspicious person... And it's
not like I'm trying to pick up girls or
anything...

I start to panic as I fumble around with the
pockets of my jacket, desperately searching for my
business card holder, but it's nowhere to be
found.
\n<Minato Neon>...A novice performer?

\n<Sonoda Kohei>No, that's not it! Huh? That's strange... I always
keep it in my inner pocket, but... Ah!

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Damn it... Today was supposed to be my day off...
I left my business card holder at the hotel...

I remember that it was my first day off since
coming on a business trip, and I was taking a
leisurely solo trip around the station. It seems
that... I was getting excited by this unexpected
reunion.
\n<Minato Neon>...Well, you do your best too.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ah...
She tapped my shoulder and ran away...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Well... Unlike last time when things were hectic,
this time I have plenty of time, so there should
be plenty of opportunities.)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Next, I'll follow the proper procedure... Huh?)

I can feel the gaze from my surroundings. Well,
that's to be expected... From an outsider's
perspective, it must look like a failed attempt at
picking up someone. Standing there alone, I must
look quite ridiculous.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(No, I'm not trying to pick up anyone... Please
don't look at me like that...)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」

And then... unable to bear it any longer, I fled
from that place as if running away...

Four months ago... When I was staying at the
business trip destination for about three days for
various procedures, I met her.

\#...It was truly love at first sight. I happened
to see her playing the guitar in front of the
station, and I just stopped by out of curiosity.
But... before I knew it, I was captivated.

People who were touched by the same strings as me
also stopped in their tracks, in the cold sky
where \# snow began to fall... Everyone was
captivated by her singing.

\#...I closed my eyes. And then... your figure
singing in front of a large crowd became clear in
my mind's eye.

I was too embarrassed to say this to you in the
end, \#, but at that time... I had a premonition
of your shining future.

I wonder what she is doing now? Is she lying in
bed just like me? And... I hope she is sleeping
peacefully.

Even though we were always together, now it feels
like that is no longer possible. Even though we
are in the same mansion, I feel a distance greater
than just physical distance.

I want to meet and talk... Now... I feel like I
can say it now. You, who shines brighter every
day, are so dazzling that it makes me, an ordinary
person, feel inferior... There are words that I
haven't been able to convey because of my
inferiority complex.
Since that time, I have always...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Wow... That's amazing. It seems like it can earn
quite a lot.

Neon, who had thrown the tip into the piggy bank
in the empty base case and finished preparing to
go home, stood up.
\n<Minato Neon>Hehe, today I'll have croquettes with dinner.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Huh... It seems like you're quite desperate...

\n<Minato Neon>Most of my part-time job earnings go towards
activity funds...

Well, that's true... There are instrument
maintenance costs and case fees. Generally, there
is a perception that student band members are
poor. Especially since she was living alone, it
was even more so.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>......Do you want to go grab a meal?

I couldn't help but feel sorry for her dinner
situation, so I unintentionally invited her. I
really didn't mean anything else, but I guess it
can be interpreted that way.
\n<Minato Neon>What?! Of course, you're treating me, right?!

...I was surprised when Neon unexpectedly got on,
but I was relieved that she didn't think I was
trying to pick her up. I wonder if I've been able
to gain some trust by hiding my identity and going
there for almost a year?
\n<Minato Neon>Hey... Can I choose the restaurant?
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Hmm... Ah, I don't mind...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Well... If I think of it as a commemoration of
realizing that I have gained trust, this level of
expense is cheap.)

I don't really have a significant income... But
thanks to not having any hobbies and not having
much desire for material things, I had some
savings.

Therefore, I had become excited. I was looking
forward to what kind of famous restaurant she
would take me to.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」
\n<Minato Neon>Hehe, it's been a while since I've eaten out♪

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(What... what's with this girl... is she here to
make me cry?)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Um... Is it okay? Since it's a special occasion,
how about going to a local restaurant known for
its delicious food?
\n<Minato Neon>Hmm... What's wrong? Let's go already!

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Well... I like it too, but I go there 2-3 times a
week...)

\n<Minato Neon>There are so many options... I'm not sure what to
choose...

Minato Neon, with a frowning face, was staring at
the menu. They seemed to be greatly troubled about
what to eat.

\n<Minato Neon>The set meals are tempting, but I feel like having
beef bowl...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>It seems like you can choose the toppings too.
\n<Minato Neon>What did you say... nuguuuguu...

...It seems like it will take a while longer. I
took out my smartphone and decided to kill time
for now.

\n<Minato Neon>Alright, I've decided on the large beef bowl.
Simple is best. What will Sonoda-san order?

\n<Sonoda Kohei>I'll have the regular... Oh, maybe I'll add an egg
too.

\n<Minato Neon>...Huh? Are you saying we have to line up... for a
regular-sized beef bowl?
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Huh... well... then, let's call the waiter.
\n<Minato Neon>Wait a minute!

Minato Neon, with a fierce expression, grabbed my
hand as I reached for the call button.

\n<Minato Neon>Sonoda-san, are you getting the large serving?
You're a bit on the skinny side, so you should eat
a lot...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Why is that? I always get the regular size. Let
go... huh?! What strength...

...Neon's fingertips sank into the back of my
hand. Just before pressing the button, my hand
stopped and couldn't move even a bit.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ouch... It's not good to leave bruises, you
know...
\n<Minato Neon>But...

\n<Minato Neon>Uwaa... They'll probably think I'm a big eater or
something, being a girl and ordering a size bigger
than the guys! (laughs)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>The waiter doesn't really care about that kind of
thing...

\n<Minato Neon>I'll take care of the order because I'm the one
who's concerned.

\n<Minato Neon>I'll have a large serving and a special serving of
beef bowl with two eggs. Oh, and also one regular
serving for takeout, please.
\n<Shop Assistant>Understood~. We have received your order...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(This guy... not only casually added extra eggs
for himself, but also ordered a bento...)
\n<Minato Neon>Hehe, it's been a while since I had beef bowl♪
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Sigh... That's unfair. If you show me that
expression, I won't be able to say anything...)

parameters.name: コンビニ・入店チャイム01

parameters:
\n<Minato Neon>Thank you for the meal♪ I feel bad for having you
buy souvenirs for me.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(That's something you ordered on your own, right?
Well, um... it's fine now...)

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(......Isn't this the perfect timing? I can't deny
that it feels like you're luring me with
food...but I'll just close my eyes to that.)

\n<Minato Neon>Thank you for today. Well then, see you at the
next street live...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>...Wait a minute!

I called out to Neon from behind. My voice might
have gotten a little louder.
\n<Minato Neon>What...? I'm not giving back this bento now...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>I won't do such a thing! No, that's not it...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ahem... Excuse me. I've been silent until now, but
I am this kind of person...

Handing over the business card that I couldn't
give her at that time.
\n<Minato Neon>\r[ Production...?
\n<Sonoda Kohei>...Minato Neon-san, I... came here to scout you.

\# I want to deliver your song to the world... Let
me... No, allow me to help with that!
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Uwaaaaaahhh!! I bit ittttt!!)
\n<Minato Neon>Please give it to me...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Please give it to me...

No, maybe it was too familiar... I got scared at
the last moment and ended up forcefully changing
direction while talking. It was a line I had
practiced over and over again, my special line...

\n<Minato Neon>No... There's also the possibility of it being a
dialect...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Well then, in that direction...
\n<Minato Neon>Puff... There's no way that's true.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Ku... This person... I endured the embarrassment
and tried to support them, but they betrayed me in
seconds...)
\n<Minato Neon>Well then, see you again... Thanks for today.

Neon waved her hand lightly and disappeared into
the station premises with a quick run.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」

Her response was Give me time. Well, that's
understandable. She's still a student and has
plenty of options for the future. It's not easy
for someone to make a quick decision to live based
on their special skills.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(......I guess I'll wait for a contact for now)

Finally, I felt relieved by the progress that had
been made, but deep down, I was anxious. The
business trip period of one year in this town was
coming to an end in less than a month.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Maybe I've been too cautious... No, that's not
it. This... is probably not good as a scout...)

\#...I think I was just purely enjoying the little
time I spent with her. \#I was scared of losing
that little time. \#\! I think this feeling of
loss that was born in my heart... maybe, that's
what it is.

During a time when I have to consider the
handover, my free time is being reduced by \r[
days.

After somehow managing to arrange my schedule, I
headed towards the plaza in front of the station.
However, ever since that day... from the corner of
the plaza, which was her usual spot, only her
figure was noticeably missing.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(She's not here today... Did something happen? If
only I had asked for her contact information...)

I might have been a little too optimistic. I had
assumed that I would receive some kind of contact
right away. I'm disgusted with my own shallowness,
being satisfied with just handing over my business
card.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(No... Maybe this is her answer. Perhaps I scared
her by getting too close...)

I looked out over the empty plaza in front of the
station. And then... I saw two men who seemed to
be band members setting up for a street live
performance in that space.

I couldn't bear the sight of that everyday scene,
as if she had never been there from the
beginning... I left the plaza as if escaping.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>...  Note: The ellipsis (...) indicates a pause or
hesitation in speech.

Last night, I had a small farewell party and ended
up drinking a little too much, so now I'm being
attacked by a slight headache.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Sigh... Maybe I should buy some headache medicine
on the way...)

I finished all the handover tasks and was able to
successfully complete my business trip. Today and
tomorrow are completely off, so all I have to do
is go home. I indulged in a lazy nap until early
afternoon.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(It's been a year... It feels like it went by in
an instant...)

I looked up at the hotel that took care of me for
a year and muttered in my heart.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>...Well, I guess I'll go home.

I will head towards the main street. When going to
the station, I always used the bus, but today I
want to walk while indulging in sentimentality.

And then... as I walked confidently, a bus passed
me and stopped at the bus stop ahead of my gaze.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(If I run, will I make it? No, I've decided to
walk...)

Deciding firmly to see off the bus, I continue
walking. However, the bus doesn't seem to depart
at all, and the distance between me and the bus
keeps getting closer.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Hmph... I know. If I run, they'll close the doors
right before I reach them, and I'll have to
awkwardly ask them to open them again and become
the center of attention among the passengers! I
won't fall for that trick!)

\n<In-car announcement>We will be stopping for about 1 minute for time
adjustment. Please wait a moment.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Ah, I'll get on)... Hm...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>「.........」

On a Saturday afternoon, the square was quite
lively, and I walked through it, looking around.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Is it feminine... but...)

I want to meet Neon. Even if she's avoiding me, I
at least want to greet her.

However... She was nowhere to be found, not even
in the usual spot in the square. It's
disappointing that I couldn't greet her, but I
won't be discouraged. Because I'm sure we'll meet
in the near future.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Even if I don't do anything, someone should be
able to find Neon. And then, maybe we'll even
appear together on TV... No, perhaps someone from
my family will also be involved...)

At that moment, I apologized briefly and left the
square with a peaceful feeling, hoping that we
could have a chat about old times...

I heard the sound of a message notification coming
from the bag hanging on my shoulder.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(I have to put down my bag to take out my work
phone, so maybe I should check it on the train...)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Persistent... This sound is a message, right?)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ah, excuse me...

I almost bumped into someone and apologized. They
were playing with their smartphone while walking,
so technically I didn't have to apologize...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Ugh, so persistent! Is this a prank message?!)

I set down my belongings on the seat that was
installed in the hallway, and took out my
smartphone.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Who is this... It's an unfamiliar email
address...)
I started checking the received emails one by one.
Where are you right now, \#?
Hey, \#.
Ah, there you are.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>(Huh... No, what is this? It's scary...)
\n<Sonoda Kohei>L-Let's pretend we didn't see anything...
\n<？？？>Don't do it, and don't put away your smartphone!
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Eek!

I was suddenly called out and unintentionally let
out a voice. With fear, I turned around, and
there... she was.
\n<Minato Neon>What the... What do you mean by 'hii' me...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>...Neon? No, look at this...

I turned my smartphone towards her and showed her
the received emails one by one.
\n<Minato Neon>Huh... scary... Wait, isn't this the email I sent!
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Is it you?! How confusing!
\n<Minato Neon>「.........」
\n<Minato Neon>By the way, 'hii'... what does that mean?
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Don't say that...
\n<Minato Neon>Alright, then let's go.
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Are we going... with that luggage...
A large suitcase was placed at Neon's feet.

\n<Minato Neon>Hey... don't play dumb about \r[ now, okay? I
won't let you pretend it didn't happen...
\n<Sonoda Kohei>No way... Are you planning to come with me?

\n<Minato Neon>Ah, that's the plan. I quit school and my part-
time job for that purpose, and I even moved out of
my house and convinced my parents. It was tough,
you know...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>No no no no... Before that, couldn't you have at
least contacted me once...
\n<Minato Neon>I thought I'd surprise you ♪
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Ngh... guh...

I was at a loss for words... Various emotions
overwhelmed me, and I didn't have time to feel the
joy of our reunion.

\n<Sonoda Kohei>There are many complaints I want to make... but
why is today the day you're coming back...

\n<Minato Neon>I heard it from the staff at Onomichi Production,
so it's definitely decided, right? Oh, make sure
to coordinate our story later, pretending to be my
girlfriend.

It's not that big of a production. Her story must
have already spread within the company...

\n<Sonoda Kohei>I understand... Well, that's fine too... By the
way, do you have a place to stay over there?

\n<Minato Neon>Until I find a place to live, take care of me ♪
Come on, let's go!
\n<Sonoda Kohei>Hey, wait a minute! What the... hey, Neon!

And so... And so... As spring comes to an end and
the cherry blossoms begin to turn green, our story
began with the arrival of summer----...
